  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Reinforcement Learning
Category:    Paradigm
Definition:  Agent learns from environment interaction to maximize reward
Year:        1950
Researchers: Bellman; Sutton/Barto
Applications:Games, robotics, recommendations, LLM alignment
Related:     Reward, policy, value function, Q-learning

Concept:     Transformer
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Attention-based model processing sequences in parallel
Year:        2017
Researchers: Vaswani et al.
Applications:LLMs, vision models, protein folding
Related:     GPT, BERT, attention mechanism

Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Godel's Incompleteness
Branch:       Logic
Formula:      Every consistent system has unprovable true statements
Applications: AI limits, foundations of math
Discoverer:   Kurt Godel (1931)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

